# The One Power · the True Source that turns the Wheel

The One Power is the energy drawn from the True Source, and it is the force that drives the Wheel and weaves the Pattern. It is split into two halves: saidin, the male half, and saidar, the female — equal and opposite, two parts of a single whole. Those who can wield it weave it in five threads: Earth, Air, Fire, Water, and Spirit, and from these threads all the works of channeling are made.

The Power is not given freely. At the Breaking of the World, the Dark One's counterstroke fell upon saidin and tainted it, so that for three thousand years any man who channeled was driven inexorably to madness. The female half remained clean, but the cost of the Power is universal: to reach too far, or to be forced beyond endurance, is to burn out forever and lose the ability to touch the Source at all.

Yet to wield the One Power is to live more fully than other folk — more light, more life, the senses heightened and the world made keener. It is at once the saga's greatest gift and its sharpest danger, the thing that exalts and the thing that destroys.

Its nature of emergence is electrical: the One Power is the channeled force itself, the living current that runs through the world and turns the Wheel — energy drawn, threaded, and loosed, the very flow of creation made into a tool in mortal hands.
